Package aston.group20.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAircraft
    The IAircraft class defines the functionality that all Aircrafts share, including both the currently implemented Powered and Unpowered Aircraft classes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AirControlTower
    The Air Control Tower class manages the queues containing the active aircraft; it ensures that the aircraft within the queues are sorted correctly based on the strategy comparator that was passed through from the Airport class.
    Aircraft
    The Aircraft class implements the IAircraft interface and contains the fields and the majority of method implementation; however it still has the two types of Aircraft below it as well as the concrete subclasses.
    Airport  
    CommercialAircraft
    This class defines the characteristics of Commercial Aircraft, including the landing time, the takeoff time and the length of time that it can fly for/it's fuel level.
    Counter
    The Counter class is used to store and display information for the final report when the GUI is run
    FuelStrategy  
    Glider
    This class defines the characteristics of Gliders, including both the landing time and the takeoff It extends the abstract class UnpoweredAircraft and is a concrete subclass.
    Hangar
    The Hangar class is used to create aircrafts as well as assigning the probabilities of each aircraft being created
    LightAircraft
    This class defines the characteristics of Light Aircraft, including the landing time, the takeoff time and the length of time that it can fly for/it's fuel level.
    PoweredAircraft
    Characterizes the shared behaviours of all powered aircraft fulfills the inheritence of the Aircraft class
    Runway
    The Runway class is used to accommodate Aircraft taking off and landing; it is simple yet critical to the Simulation.
    Simulator  
    Strategy
    The Strategy class is used to define how aircrafts should be sorted as well as how they should land and take off
    UnpoweredAircraft
    Characterizes the shared behaviours of all Unpowered aircraft fulfills the inheritence of the Aircraft class
    WaitingTimeStrategy
    The Waiting Time Strategy class is used to identify the waiting time for each aircraft it fulfills the inheritence of the Strategy class
